# FastAPI Standards

## CORS — never use wildcard
```python
app.add_middleware(
    CORSMiddleware,
    allow_origins=[settings.allowed_origin],  # from env var
    allow_methods=["POST", "GET"],
    allow_headers=["Content-Type", "Accept"],
)
```

## Rate limiting
Use slowapi. 10/minute/IP on POST routes.
```python
from slowapi import Limiter
from slowapi.util import get_remote_address
limiter = Limiter(key_func=get_remote_address)

@app.post("/analyze")
@limiter.limit("10/minute")
async def analyze(...): ...
```

## Health endpoint (required)
```python
@app.get("/health")
async def health():
    return {"status": "ok", "version": "1.0.0"}
```
This is called by Lovable on page load to pre-warm Railway.
Never disable or rename this endpoint.

## Error responses
AgentCallError      → HTTP 422 with error detail
SchemaValidationError → HTTP 422 with error detail
Unexpected exception → HTTP 500 with generic message
Never expose raw Python tracebacks in responses.

## Async
All endpoints must be async def.
LLM calls use await.
